BT 1 0 0 1 0 74 Tm .928651 Tw 12 TL /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( is a convenient way to create an execution context in place where you need it.) Tj T* 0 Tw .917485 Tw (However, including it as the sole, standard way to obtain execution resources on the host may promote) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.486412 Tw (bad practice that will inadvertently lead to oversubscription and poor composability. In this section, we) Tj T* 0 Tw 4.14816 Tw (outline some of the weaknesses of ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( and describe characteristics that an) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.920697 Tw (alternative execution context should possess to avoid these weaknesses. We are not arguing for the) Tj T* 0 Tw .678555 Tw (removal of ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( from P0443 but instead to complement it with at least one additional) Tj T* 0 Tw (choice.) Tj T* ET
