BT 1 0 0 1 0 74 Tm 2.316136 Tw 12 TL /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The first issue with ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( is that it can easily lead to oversubscription. Real-world) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.01814 Tw (applications are complicated and, in general, link with many third party libraries. Any shared object \(.so\) as) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.613828 Tw (well as an application itself may create its own ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (. Without alternatives in the) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.869984 Tw (standard, this might in fact seem like the only portable choice. However when there are many) Tj T* 0 Tw .309069 Tw /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( instances, the end application will likely, inadvertently request more threads than) Tj T* 0 Tw 5.903314 Tw (the number of physical cores available in the hardware, oversubscribing the hardware. For) Tj T* 0 Tw (compute-intense workloads, oversubscription often leads to poor performance.) Tj T* ET
