BT 1 0 0 1 0 146 Tm .012765 Tw 12 TL /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The second problem is that even if an alternative context is specified, there is no clean way to composably) Tj T* 0 Tw .012927 Tw (construct software to use it. Imagine that an application wants to use OpenMP as the main parallel context) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.01668 Tw (and wants the third party libraries that it calls to also use OpenMP for parallelism. How does an application) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.55832 Tw (share this choice with a third party library? An obvious solution is for the third party library to support) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.908443 Tw (executors through its interfaces, but even so, the current proposals for executors would require) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.960697 Tw (applications to pass executors or execution contexts through the function parameters. But it may not) Tj T* 0 Tw .464985 Tw (always be possible or convenient to pass the execution context through the call stack. The executors are) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.181567 Tw (not the option since querying the context is optional but \(as it will be shown below library needs to get) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.000539 Tw (properties of the execution context and it needs them at run-time \(if it's .so\). Of course it would be possible) Tj T* 0 Tw .462976 Tw (to support only ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg ( instances, but as we've already argued, ) Tj /F3 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg (static_thread_pool) Tj /F1 10 Tf 0 0 0 rg  T* 0 Tw 1.260988 Tw (should not be the only choice. And even if it were the only choice. The idea is to support the arbitrary) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.021265 Tw (execution context. Thus, we need a standard interface for it: either virtual interface for execution context or) Tj T* 0 Tw (polymorphic wrapper over it.) Tj T* ET
